## Context

- crc-liquid-biopsy-panel: Project in analysis phase. Completed cMCD comparison and stage stratification.
- Task 1087 (cMCD comparison): 17/21 cMCD genes overlap with our data (81%). 4 genes (BMP3, APC, MGMT, RASSF1) filtered by delta-beta >= 0.3 but have significant cfDNA signal. Sensitivity gap (47.7% vs 87.82%) is architectural — protein-only panel vs methylation. Created developer tasks #1212 (lower threshold) and #1213 (build methylation classifier).
- Task 1088 (stage stratification): Detection CpGs have ZERO staging power (AUC=0.517). Stage discrimination requires different features than detection. Created developer task #1214 (stage-specific features) and data curator task #1215 (stage-annotated cfDNA data).
- Task 1089 (threshold analysis): Previously completed by prior analyst run. 7-protein panel at 90% spec reaches 67.8% sensitivity.
- Created research_director review task #1216 for strategic decision: close detection sensitivity gap first vs pursue staging.
- Key outputs: cmcd_comparison_report.json, stage_stratification_results.json in output/diagnostics/crc-liquid-biopsy-panel/
- No pending analyst tasks remain for this project.
- Next: wait for developer to rebuild pipeline with lower threshold and methylation classifier, then re-evaluate combined panel performance.
